{start_of_verse}
[C]  So, so you think you can t[D/F#]ell,
Heaven from H[Am/E]ell, blue skies from pa[G]in.
Can you tell a green [D/F#]field from a cold steel [C]rail, a smile from a v[Am]eil,
Do you think you can t[G]ell?

{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse}
Did they get you to tr[C]ade your heroes for [D/F#]ghosts,
Hot ashes for tr[Am/E]ees, hot air for a coo[G]l breeze, cold comfort for ch[D/F#]ange,
And did you exch[C]ange a walk on part in the w[Am]ar for a lead role in a c[G]age?

[G]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse}
[C]  How I wish, how I wish you were h[D/F#]ere.
We're just [Am/E]two lost souls swimming in a fish bowl,[G] year after year,
[D/F#]    Running over the same old ground.[C] What have we found?
The same old [Am]fears. Wish you were he[G]re!

[G]  [G]
[G](fa[G]de out)
{end_of_verse}